  "time_ut": 1657641851,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dda \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dba\u0dd4\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dba\u0dd2 - \u0db4\u0dcf\u0da8\u0dbd\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mahinda should apologize publicly - Patali",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "As the activists have given President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa the opportunity to resign tomorrow (13th) due to the people's stand against a corrupt and oppressive government, Parliamentarian Patali Champika Ranawaka says that despite being given such an opportunity, he should resign peacefully without resorting to political conspiracies.",
        "He also emphasizes that Mr. Mahinda Rajapaksa, who created the Rajapakse family tree, should make a statement to the public and leave politics.",
        "He said this while commenting to the media on how to build the future political stability of the country in the face of the demands of the activists after the resignation of the President tomorrow.",
        "\"If he resigns tomorrow, a secret vote will be held in the parliament on the 20th. Currently, there are several ideas among the parties about the next government. One group says that they should control the country for the next few months, stabilize the country, and go to a general election. The fact that two people who cannot take advantage should be the president and the prime minister.",
        "Another opinion says that the main political parties, namely the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, are on one side and the Samagi Jana Balawegaya as the main opposition force is on the other side. There is an attempt to present candidates for both of them.",
        "So Mr. Sajith Premadasa has already stated his ambition. Even though Mr. Dallas Alahapperuma has not yet announced it publicly, we have seen that there is such an ambition. So, according to that, a secret election may be held on the 20th.",
        "The next strong challenge is to establish an all-party government in a formal manner and take steps to change this bad situation. So I think all the parliamentary parties should join it. Our hope is that by the 20th, on the basis of an agreement, the president and the prime minister will be appointed and a stable government will be established, and after an interim program, a general election will be given to the people.",
        "It is a great service to the people in the struggle ground to drive out the Rajapaksa people, the people of this country did something that the opposition and political parties were unable to do. So if those people think that they should not have these 225 political parties. In the coming general election, the will of the people should be tested and they should take over the governance of the country in the way they think is appropriate.",
        "I think now is the time for the Prime Minister to make a decision. The only thing that should happen is that he should step down after giving space to an all-party government in the parliament. We hope it will be implemented.\""
      ],
